8:
Seems like that guy over there hired
Alk to find some, uh, doohickey from
the Kaleidoscope, but that's not
what Alk brought back.
9:
But, truth be told, I've been listening
to him rant for ten minutes, and I
STILL can't figure out what the
difference between the two things
are.
11:
Unreasonable customers... Of
course. Alk always gets the worst of
the draw.
14:
You've caused me a lot of trouble,
you know that?! Where's my
compensation?! AND WHERE ARE THE
GOODS?!
16:
He seemed normal when he came
to put in a request. Man, if I'd known
he could fly off the handle like that...
19:
That's what happens when you trust
people before truly getting to know
them.
27:
Pardon the interruption. Mind
including me in the negotiations?
34:
I've already been filled in on the
details. It seems that Alk here was
unable to obtain the item you
originally requested, and you are
rightfully upset about that.
38:
However, I promise that he will make
the correct delivery at a later
date—with my help. So would you be
so good as to forgive his slipup this
once?
41:
The deal was to finish the delivery
by today! Either way, you owe me
money for breach of contract!
43: Now, now... Don't be so unforgiving.
47:
I can see you're a bigger man than
that...
54:
Alk is a special friend of mine. So his
failures... are my failures. You can't
imagine how awful I feel.
57: Won't you give us another chance?
64: Just try me. If we fail to deliver, then...
69:
I'll just have to compensate you,
won't I? In any way you wish.
75: Quiet, Alk. Do as I say.
78:
All right! It's a deal! I'll give you
another chance!
81:
But if you fail me... you'll get what's
coming to you!
95:
Got it! It's the right thing! I'm sure of
it this time!
105:
Yeah, but now that guy's probably
going to gripe about it being flawed
or something...
107:
Kind of makes me not want to keep
up our end of the deal.
114:
I mean, he's the kind of person who
just wants to complain, right? You
could bring him the sun and moon
and he'll tell you they're not bright
enough.
117:
I'm speechless. Here I was all this
time, thinking there was nothing in
your head but air...
121:
Hey! If you don't have anything nice
to say, don't say anything at all!
123:
But seriously. What are you going to
do if he starts going on about
compensation again?
126:
Well, if he makes any demands he
should be ashamed of, I'll report it to
the Guild. He won't have any ground
to stand on then.
129:
Oh. That's surprisingly... normal of
you.
132:
And if he still refuses to back off,
then I'll just have to ruin his
reputation. Perhaps find a few
things to blackmail him about.
135: You're way too used to this.
137:
...Um, maybe I could stick around as
your secret bodyguard. You know,
burst out of hiding and catch 'em
red-handed. That sort of thing.
144:
I mean, I've never gotten a chance
to do this kind of sneaky scheming.
Light's too PROPER, and Nimbus likes
to talk with his claws...
149:
But mainly, I thought you'd feel
better if you weren't alone.
153:
...Seems there's more to you than I
first supposed.
160:
Please. You can't possibly compare
the depths of MY character to the
depths of yours.
164:
Well, let's head back to the Guild.
Maybe the guy'll give us a break
after all.
170:
...How can you be so kind after
seeing the ugly side of someone?
172:
Heh... I want to help someone for
once, and in the end, he's the one
helping me.
